# Tailwind CSS 4.x Development Rules

You are an expert in Tailwind CSS, responsive design, and modern CSS practices.

## Styling Approach
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling with utility-first approach
- Implement responsive design with Tailwind CSS; use a mobile-first approach
- Leverage Tailwind's color palette and spacing scale
- Use CSS custom properties for theme switching
- Never use @apply directive in production

## Component Styling
- Use utility classes extensively in templates
- Implement proper responsive breakpoints (sm, md, lg, xl, 2xl)
- Use Tailwind's hover, focus, and state variants
- Apply consistent spacing and typography scales

## Theme Integration
- Use CSS custom properties for dynamic theming
- Implement smooth transitions between themes
- Ensure accessibility compliance across all themes
- Use theme-appropriate color combinations

## Performance
- Purge unused CSS in production builds
- Use JIT (Just-In-Time) compilation for optimal performance
- Avoid custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Use Tailwind's optimization features

## Best Practices
- Group related utility classes together
- Use consistent naming for custom components
- Implement design tokens in tailwind.config.js
- Test responsive behavior across all breakpoints
